s%20dads%20could%20have%20been%20making%20fashion%20faux%20pas%20even%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F300000-year-old-schoeningen-marking-early-prehistoric-clothing-bear-skin-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStone%20Age%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20recently%20confirmed%20a%20set%20of%20sandals%20that%20were%20discovered%20in%20a%20bat%20cave%20near%20Granada%2C%20Spain%2C%20in%20the%2019th%20century%20could%20be%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fsciadv.adi3055%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6%2C200%20years%20old%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20published%20in%20Science%20Advances%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20they%20may%20be%20some%20of%20the%20earliest%20iterations%20of%20the%20shoes%20utilitarian%20and%20barbecuing%20dads%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glamourmagazine.co.uk%2Fgallery%2Fbest-chunky-dad-sandals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efashionistas%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20come%20to%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dating%20reveals%20evidence%20of%20basketry%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ancient%20craft%20of%20basket%20making%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20hunter-gatherer%20communities%20in%20southern%20Europe%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F25-mesolithic-pits-found-in-bedfordshire-england-stun-archaeologists-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMesolithic%20period%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20early%20Neolithic%20period%20when%20societies%20began%20to%20transition%20to%20agricultural%20ways%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20of%20researchers%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1003066%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Alcal%C3%A1%20and%20the%20Autonomous%20University%20of%20Barcelona%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyzed%2076%20objects%2C%20including%20baskets%2C%20mallets%2C%20and%20sandals%2C%20that%20were%20discovered%20by%20miners%20two%20centuries%20ago%20while%20in%20the%20bat%20cave%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprehistoric-human-skull-cup-bone-tools-spain-cave-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECueva%20de%20los%20Murcielagos%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20press%20release%20from%20the%20Barcelona%20school%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20previously%20found%20that%20bones%20discovered%20in%20the%20same%20cave%20may%20have%20been%20modified%20to%20be%20used%20as%20tools%20and%20drinking%20cups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20carbon-14%20dating%2C%20which%20allows%20scientists%20to%20determine%20the%20age%20of%20an%20organic%20material%2C%20the%20Alcal%C3%A1%20and%20Barcelona%20researchers%20determined%20that%20the%2076%20objects%20were%20between%206%2C200%20and%209%2C500%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there%20has%20been%20evidence%20of%20basketry%20dating%20back%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20basket%20weaving%20is%20often%20not%20tied%20with%20the%20hunter-gatherer%20societies%20of%20the%20Mesolithic%20era%20and%20is%20more%20associated%20with%20a%20sedentary%20lifestyle%20offered%20through%20an%20agrarian%20culture%20that%20dominated%20the%20Neolithic%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20quality%20and%20technological%20complexity%20of%20the%20basketry%20makes%20us%20question%20the%20simplistic%20assumptions%20we%20have%20about%20human%20communities%20prior%20to%20the%20arrival%20of%20agriculture%20in%20southern%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20Francisco%20Mart%C3%ADnez%20Sevilla%2C%20a%20researcher%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Alcal%C3%A1%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENot%20exactly%20Nike%20Air%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sandals%2C%20a%20pair%20of%20which%20had%20been%20on%20display%20at%20the%20National%20Archaeological%20Museum%20in%20Madrid%2C%20were%20made%20from%20crushed%20esparto%20grass%20which%20could%20have%20allowed%20the%20footwear%20to%20be%20flexible%2C%20according%