ng%20trip.%20He%20was%20my%20cousin's%20co-worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20When%20I%20moved%20to%20Sacramento%2C%20I%20moved%20in%20with%20my%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20together%20for%20three%20years%20and%20married%20for%20almost%20two.%20We%20have%20a%201-year-old%20and%20two%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20The%20prices%20in%20Sacramento%20started%20going%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20We%20were%20paying%20about%20%241%2C500%20for%20rent.%20The%20apartment%20we%20were%20living%20in%20was%20about%20900%20square%20feet.%20It%20was%20a%20two-bedroom%2C%20one-bath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGas%20at%20the%20time%20was%20about%20%246.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20It%20got%20kind%20of%20dangerous%20in%20Sacramento.%20People%20were%20breaking%20into%20our%20cars.%20One%20of%20our%20windows%20got%20broken%20into%20and%20they%20drilled%20into%20the%20gas%20tank%20of%20the%20other%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20We%20had%20to%20get%20that%20fixed%20and%20it%20cost%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20I%20was%20pregnant%20with%20my%20daughter%20and%20once%20you%20have%20a%20baby%20that%20makes%20it%20even%20scarier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20I%20had%20always%20sort%20of%20wanted%20to%20move%20out%20of%20California.%20I%20wanted%20to%20move%20to%20Texas%20but%20I%20was%20open%20to%20anywhere.%20I%20brought%20it%20up%20one%20day%20and%20she%20said%20we%20should%20do%20it.%20That%20was%20early%20on%20in%20our%20relationship.%20It%20didn't%20become%20serious%20until%20maybe%20about%20three%20months%20before%20we%20actually%20moved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20pretty%20adventurous.%20Part%20of%20wanting%20to%20move%20was%20venturing%20out%2C%20part%20was%20the%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20and%20part%20of%20it%20was%20political.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20looked%20at%20several%20different%20states%2C%20like%20Arizona%20and%20Florida.%20We%20wanted%20somewhere%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmoved-california-to-texas-will-never-go-back-expensive-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efelt%20comfortable%20raising%20our%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-california-texas-conservative-affordable-realtor-helps-others-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancially%20affordable%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20decided%20Texas%20was%20the%20best%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20initially%20moved%20to%20Tyler%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20We%20never%20visited%20before%20moving.%20We%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20everywhere%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20for%20Texas.%20The%20first%20job%20I%20got%20was%20the%20one%20I%20took.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20drove%20down%20here%20on%20January%201%20with%20both%20our%20dogs.%20My%20wife%20flew%20with%20the%20baby%20a%20few%20days%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20I%20was%20a%20little%20nervous%20about%20the%20move.%20I%20was%20used%20to%20being%20around%20my%20family.%20Now%20that%20we%20weren't%20going%20to%20have%20anyone%20around%20I%20was%20a%20little%20scared.%20But%20mostly%20I%20was%20excited%20for%20a%20brand%20new%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20Tyler%20was%20great.%20It%20was%20very%20family-oriented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20I%20was%20able%20to%20meet%20a%20mom's%20group%20and%20have%20a%20support%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20It%20was%20a%20great%20environment.%20But%20we%20were%20missing%20that%20big%20city%20feel.%20There%20was%20only%20a%20Sam's%20Club%20out%20there.%20My%20wife%20is%20Vietnamese%20and%20she%20loves%20cultural%20food.%20They%20didn't%20have%20too%20many%20options%20up%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20airport%20was%20an%20hour%20and%20forty-five%20minutes%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20stayed%20in%20Tyler%20for%20about%20eight%20months.%20We%20knew%20it%20wasn't%20going%20to%20be%20forever.%20We're%20not%20really%20people%20who%20settle.%20If%20we%20get%20something%20in%20our%20mind%20then%20we%20just%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20for%20jobs%20again.%20I%20went%20with%20a%20private%20consultant%20that%20let%20us%20choose%20where%20in%20the%20state%20we%20wanted%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brittany%20Casillas-Ta%20said%20she%20feels%20safer%20bringing%20her%201-year-old%20daughter%20out%20and%20about%20in%20Texas%20than%20she%20did%20in%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651759955640b20019d78915%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrittany%20Casillas-Ta%20said%20she%20feels%20safer%20bringing%20her%201-year-old%20daughter%20out%20and%20about%20in%20Texas%20than%20she%20did%20in%20California.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brittany%20Casillas-Ta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20moved%20again%20three%20weeks%20ago.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20Now%20we%20live%20in%20Houston.%20It's%20huge%20but%20also%20affordable.%20We%20felt%20like%20Houston%20maintained%20that%20affordability%20and%20also%20provided%20everything%20we%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20paying%20%241%2C245%20for%20a%20townhouse%20here.%20It's%20two%20floors%2C%20two%20bedrooms%2C%20and%20three%20and%20a%20half%20bathrooms.%20It's%20got%20a%20huge%20living%20room%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20We%20had%20half%20a%20kitchen%20back%20in%20Sacramento.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20We%20live%20adjacent%20to%20a%20very%20nice%20community%20with%20mansions.%20It's%20just%20a%20really%20nice%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20Making%20friends%20has%20been%20the%20hardest%20thing.%20We've%20been%20trying%20to%20explore%20on%20the%20weekends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20Thankfully%2C%20people%20are%20super%20nice%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20car%20broke%20down%2C%20which%20was%20really%20unfortunate.%20But%20one%20of%20my%20co-workers%20gave%20me%20a%20ride%20to%20work%20for%20two%20months.%20People%20are%20so%20kind%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrittany%3A%20In%20California%2C%20people%20mind%20their%20own%20business.%20They're%20just%20heads%20down.%20But%20here%2C%20people%20will%20stop%20and%20ask%20how%20you're%20doing.%20They're%20really%20thoughtful%20and%20they%20really%20do%20care.%20I%20like%20it%20here%20a%20lot%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20welcoming%20and%20willing%20to%20help%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20more%20babies%20for%20our%20daughter%20to%20play%20with%20here%20and%20places%20for%20her%20to%20go.%20She%20just%20turned%20one%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20go%20out%20that%20much%20in%20Sacramento%20because%20it%20cost%20money%20and%20I%20didn't%20feel%20really%20safe%20going%20to%20the%20parks.%20Now%20I'm%20able%20to%20take%20her%20out.%20She%20gets%20to%20be%20around%20more%20people%20and%20have%20that%20exposure%20and%20socialization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222784%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20family%20was%20able%20to%20visit%20Disney%20World%20last%20month%20for%20their%20daughter's%20birthday.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651759cb5640b20019d7891e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221856%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20family%20was%20able%20to%20visit%20Disney%20World%20last%20month%20for%20their%20daughter's%20birthday.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brittany%20Casillas-Ta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20were%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%20in%20California.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%3A%20It%20was%20very%20hard.%20We%20couldn't%20do%20anything.%20We%20weren't%20able%20to%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20car%20got%20broken%20into%20in%20California%2C%20it%20was%20really%20expensive%20and%20hard%20to%20financially%20recover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20in%20Texas%2C%20our%20Toyota%20broke%20down%20and%20it%20sucked%20but%20it%20didn't%20feel%20like%20it%20was%20the%20end%2