y%2Fitaly-wants-migrant-rescue-ships-sent-back-to-countries-funding-their-operation-12972650%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fitaly-wants-migrant-rescue-ships-sent-back-to-countries-funding-their-operation-12972650%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fitaly-wants-migrant-rescue-ships-sent-back-to-countries-funding-their-operation-12972650%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Afghan%20Envoy%20Confirms%20News%20of%20Embassy%20in%20Delhi%20Shutting%20Down%2C%20Consulates%20to%20Remain%20Open%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F15151808%2FAfghan_embassy_Delhi_1069.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20asserts%20that%20it%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20verifying%20the%20letter%E2%80%99s%20authenticity%2C%20the%20Afghan%20ambassador%20has%20confirmed%20his%20intention%20to%20close%20the%20embassy%20by%20the%20upcoming%20weekend.%20However%2C%20the%20two%20other%20consulates%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Hyderabad%2C%20which%20have%20established%20relations%20with%20the%20Taliban%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20ministry%20in%20Kabul%2C%20maintain%20that%20they%20are%20still%20operational.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20statement%20sent%20by%20the%20Afghan%20ambassador%20to%20India%2C%20Farid%20Mamundzay%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20affirm%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20communications%2C%20acknowledging%20that%20the%20content%20may%20be%20met%20with%20reservation%20by%20the%20MEA.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20communication%20in%20question%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fafghan-embassy-to-close-new-delhi-mea-taliban-farid-mamundzay%5C%22%3Enote%20verbale%3C%2Fa%3E%20dated%20September%2025%2C%20which%20was%20leaked%20and%20circulated%20on%20social%20media.%20It%20was%20addressed%20to%20the%20Indian%20Minister%20of%20External%20Affairs%20and%20conveyed%20the%20embassy%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20shutter%20its%20premises%20in%20New%20Delhi%20by%20September%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20letter%20was%20reported%2C%20MEA%20sources%20had%20said%20on%20Thursday%20night%20that%20the%20content%20of%20the%20letter%20was%20being%20examined%20for%20its%20authenticity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20day%20later%2C%20Mamundzay%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20in%20London%2C%20confirmed%20the%20letter%20in%20a%20statement.%20He%20also%20added%20that%20he%20had%20been%20absent%20since%20June%2018%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20an%20Acting%20Ambassador%20actively%20overseeing%20the%20mission%E2%80%99s%20operations%20during%20this%20period%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20added%20that%20the%20departure%20of%20Afghan%20diplomats%20%E2%80%9Ccoincides%20with%20numerous%20diplomats%20coincides%20with%20an%20increasingly%20untenable%20situation%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20threats%20to%20families%20back%20in%20Afghanistan%20from%20the%20Taliban%2C%20as%20well%20as%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20support%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%20led%20to%20this%20decision.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20regrettable%20that%20India%20is%20not%20extending%20rightful%20visa%20renewals%20for%20Afghan%20diplomats%2C%20let%20alone%20considering%20their%20continued%20presence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20also%20said%20that%20conditions%20faced%20by%20Afghan%20refugees%20in%20India%20highlight%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconcerning%20aspect%E2%80%9D%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20non-membership%20in%20the%20Geneva%20Convention%20and%20its%20stance%20on%20asylum%20for%20Afghan%20citizens%20is%20a%20concerning%20aspect.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Afghan%20ambassador%E2%80%99s%20statement%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20response%20to%20remarks%20by%20Indian%20official%20sources%2C%20who%20had%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20current%20letter%20seems%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cin%20context%20of%20the%20Ambassador%20being%20out%20of%20India%20for%20past%20many%20months%2C%20steady%20departure%20of%20diplomats%20to%20third%20countries%20reportedly%20after%20receiving%20asylum%20as%20well%20as%20reports%20of%20infighting%20amongst%20Embassy%20personnel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Taliban%20took%20over%20in%20August%202021%2C%20India%20had%20evacuated%20its%20embassy%20in%20Kabul.%20However%2C%20India%20was%20back%20in%20Kabul%20in%20June%202022%20with%20a%20%E2%80%98technical%20team%E2%80%99%20made%20up%20of%20diplomats%20and%20security%20personnel.%20It%20had%20to%20work%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98de-facto%E2%80%99%20embassy%20as%20India%2C%20just%20like%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20international%20community%2C%20does%20not%20recognise%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Afghan%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20continued%20to%20operate%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%2C%20but%20did%20not%20recognise%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%20In%20May%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Taliban%20regime%20finally%20sent%20a%20directive%20that%20Farid%20Mamundzay%2C%20appointed%20by%20the%20previous%20Islamic%20Republic%2C%20should%20be%20removed%20and%20replaced%20with%20another%20diplomat%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3ECharge%20D%E2%80%99affaires%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Taliban-appointed%20diplomat%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fafghan-embassy-taliban-farid-mamundzay-mohammad-qadir-shah%5C%22%3Enot%20allowed%20to%20take%20charge%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20his%20other%20colleagues%20when%20Mamundzay%20had%20been%20out%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20received%20cold%20treatment%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FAfghanistanINHyderabad%2Fposts%2Fpfbid02NWjYn37LEdsiNePt4iemiFUz8ayNfAbKMPA6faHRTbxJniMMMiiGNBBEcdp5dQP1l%5C%22%3Ethe%20consul%20generals%3C%2Fa%3E%20met%20with%20a%20senior%20official%20in%20the%