nd%20their%20earnings%20across%20India%2C%20said%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3ECentre%20for%20Sustainable%20Employment%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20regular%20wage%20or%20salaried%20work%20tends%20to%20be%20the%20most%20remunerative%2C%20followed%20by%20self-employment%20and%20then%20casual%20wage%20work.%20Further%2C%20within%20each%20type%20of%20employment%2C%20significant%20heterogeneity%20exists%20in%20occupation%2C%20industry%2C%20and%20other%20job%20characteristics%2C%20all%20of%20which%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20determining%20labour%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29140016%2Fimage-1359.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22797%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29140016%2Fimage-1359.png%20797w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29140016%2Fimage-1359-300x123.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677487%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22328%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESocial%20disparities%20in%20labour%20earnings%20across%20social%20identities.%20Source%3A%20APU%20Report-Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20significant%20earnings%20gaps%20exist%20in%20terms%20of%20gender%2C%20caste%20and%20religion%20among%20different%20social%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20largest%20earnings%20gap%20is%20based%20on%20gender%2C%20with%20women%20reporting%20earnings%20at%20only%2040%25%20of%20those%20of%20men%20in%20self-employment%2C%20followed%20by%2064%25%20of%20men%20in%20casual%20wage%20jobs%2C%20and%2076%25%20of%20men%20in%20regular%20wage%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20gaps%20based%20on%20caste%20and%20religion%20are%20narrower%20but%20still%20significant.%20Muslims%20receive%20higher%20pay%20than%20Hindus%20in%20the%20category%20of%20casual%20wage%20labour%20but%20lower%20pay%20in%20terms%20of%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20and%20self-employment.%20There%20is%20a%20noticeable%20difference%20in%20earnings%20between%20SC%2FST%20and%20other%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29140854%2Fimage-1360.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221020%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29140854%2Fimage-1360.png%20730w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29140854%2Fimage-1360-300x179.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677490%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22608%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20APU%20Report-Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20is%20further%20broken%20down%20by%20deciles%20of%20the%20earnings%20distribution.%20As%20we%20move%20up%20the%20income%20distribution%2C%20the%20gender%20gap%20reduces%20for%20salaried%20or%20regular%20wage%20workers.%20One%20possible%20explanation%20for%20this%20trend%20could%20be%20that%20higher%20educated%20women%20have%20better%20bargaining%20positions%2C%20and%20discrimination%20is%20less%20prevalent%20in%20formal%20and%20regulated%20jobs.%20It%20also%20finds%20that%20the%20gender%20gap%20is%20much%20higher%20in%20self-employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20is%20that%20self-employed%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20engaged%20in%20lower-paying%20sectors.%20Another%20possibility%20is%20that%20self-employed%20women%20face%20more%20discrimination%20as%20compared%20to%20women%20doing%20regular%20wage%20work.%20This%20discrimination%20may%20be%20prevalent%20due%20to%20several%20factors%2C%20such%20as%20social%20norms%20that%20discourage%20women%20from%20starting%20their%20own%20businesses%2C%20or%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20credit%20and%20other%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFindings%20from%20the%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3Ealso%20suggest%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20largest%20gender%20pay%20disparity%20is%20found%20among%20the%20lowest%20income%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20that%20gender%20discrimination%20is%20most%20pronounced%20in%20the%20bottom%20quartile%20of%20the%20income%20distribution.%20Several%20factors%20may%20contribute%20to%20this%2C%20including%20that%20disadvantaged%20women%20are%20likely%20to%20work%20in%20informal%2C%20unregulated%20industries%20with%20weaker%20anti-discrimination%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143104%2Fimage-1361.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22782%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143104%2Fimage-1361.png%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143104%2Fimage-1361-300x175.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677497%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22457%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20APU%20Report-Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20focused%20on%20earnings%20gaps%20based%20on%20caste%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20religion%20in%20regular%20wage%20work%2C%20and%20analysed%20them%20on%20a%20decile-by-decile%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20showed%20that%20religion%20and%20gender-based%20pay%20gaps%20move%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction.%20Women%20at%20the%20upper%20end%20of%20the%20income%20distribution%20are%20less%20disadvantaged%20than%20men.%20However%2C%20Muslim%20workers%20at%20the%20upper%20end%20of%20the%20income%20distribution%20are%20more%20disadvantaged%20as%20compared%20to%20Hindu%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20top%20decile%20Muslim%20workers%20earn%2075%25%20of%20what%20Hindu%20workers%20earn.%20For%20the%20third%20and%20fourth%20decile%2C%20this%20number%20is%20much%20higher%20at%20around%2094%25%2C%20indicating%20that%20Muslim%20salaried%20workers%20earn%20almost%20as%20much%20as%20Hindu%20salaried%20workers%20at%20the%20lower%20end%20of%20the%20earnings%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20women%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20income%20distribution%20only%20earn%2040%25%20of%20what%20men%20earn%20but%20at%20the%20top%20decile%20the%20number%20is%2093%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20increasing%20Hindu-Muslim%20gap%20for%20higher-paid%20workers%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20significant%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29150213%2Fimage-1362.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22920%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29150213%2Fimage-1362.png%20705w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29150213%2Fimage-1362-300x196.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677506%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29150437%2Fimage-1363.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22913%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29150437%2Fimage-1363.png%20717w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29150437%2Fimage-1363-300x162.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677507%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22493%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20APU%20Report-Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20the%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20was%20highest%20in%20the%20first%20quartile%20and%20lowest%20in%20the%20fourth%20quartile%20in%202004%20%3Cem%3E(see%20the%20graph%20above)%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20suggests%20that%20gender%20discrimination%20was%20most%20severe%20among%20the%20poorest%20earners.%20The%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20narrowed%20in%20all%20quartiles%20between%202004%20and%202017.%20This%20is%20particularly%20evident%20in%20the%20second%2C%20third%2C%20and%20fourth%20quartiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20number%20of%20possible%20explanations%20for%20the%20narrowing%20of%20the%20gender%20earnings%20gap%2C%20such%20as%20increased%20awareness%20of%20gender%20discrimination%2C%20anti-discrimination%20laws%2C%20and%20changes%20in%20social%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20possibility%20could%20be%20that%20women%E2%80%99s%20educational%20attainment%20has%20increased%20significantly%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20making%20them%20more%20competitive%20in%20the%20labour%20market.%20There%20has%20also%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20available%20to%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20a%20structural%20transformation%20has%20caused%20a%20significant%20change%20in%20the%20female%20workforce%20composition.%20It%20is%20observed%20that%20older%20and%20less%20educated%20women%20are%20moving%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%20while%20younger%20and%20more%20educated%20women%20are%20increasingly%20coming%20on%20board.%20The%20change%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20earnings%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20improvements%20in%20workplace%20discrimination%20against%20women%20as%20well%20as%20shifts%20in%20the%20characteristics%20of%20those%20who%20are%20employed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20it%20can%20be%20argued%20that%20wage%20gaps%20based%20on%20gender%20can%20be%20bridged%20on%20two%20accounts%3A%20firstly%2C%20by%20reducing%20discrimination%20against%20women%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20and%20second%2C%20giving%20them%20access%20to%20higher%20education%20and%20skilled%20qualifications%2C%20making%20women%20professionally%20more%20sought%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98unexplained%20differences%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20causing%20the%20wage%20gap%20among%20two%20groups%2C%20the%20APU%20report%E2%80%99s%20authors%20employed%20the%20Blinder-Oaxaca%20decomposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20two%20main%20components%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%E2%80%9Cexplained%E2%80%9D%20component%2C%20which%20includes%20characteristics%20such%20as%20education%2C%20work%20experience%2C%20job%20tenure%2C%20etc.%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunexplained%E2%80%9D%20component%2C%20which%20includes%20factors%20such%20as%20discrimination%2C%20bias%2C%20or%20unobservable%20characteristics%20that%20affect%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20method%20highlights%20how%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunexplained%E2%80%9D%20portion%20of%20earnings%20is%20greater%20for%20women%20workers%20than%20SC%2FST%20workers%20or%20Muslim%20workers%20in%20any%20type%20of%20work.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunexplained%E2%80%9D%20earnings%20gaps%20are%20much%20larger%20based%20on%20gender%20than%20caste.%20This%20is%20because%20women%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20face%20more%20discrimination%20based%20on%20gender%20than%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECaste%20discrimination%20is%20more%20prevalent%20in%20the%20public%20sector%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3Evis%20%C3%A0%20vis%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ethe%20private%20sector%20since%20the%20latter%20runs%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20meritocracy%20as%20opposed%20to%20positive%20discrimination%20to%20empower%20groups.%20However%2C%20this%20unexplained%20gender%20disparity%20is%20more%20pronounced%20in%20rural%20areas%20as%20compared%20to%20urban%20areas.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20significant%20difference%20in%20the%20explained%20and%20unexplained%20reasons%20behind%20the%20gendered%20wage%20gaps%2C%20as%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20table%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ctable%20width%3D%5C%22624%5C%22%3E%20%3Ctbody%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3EYear%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3EExplained%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3EUnexplained%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E1983%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E36%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E64%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E1993%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E41.4%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E58.6%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E2004%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E42.3%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E57.7%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E2011%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E31.5%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E68.5%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E2017%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E16.5%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E83.5%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E2021%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E18.9%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22208%5C%22%3E81.1%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3C%2Ftbody%3E%20%3C%2Ftable%3E%20%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20APU%20Report-Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOccupational%20segregation%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOccupational%20segregation%20occurs%20when%20one%20demographic%20group%20is%20over-represented%20or%20under-represented%20in%20a%20certain%20job%20category.%20Segregation%20in%20India%20operates%20both%20vertically%20%E2%80%93%20where%20dominant%20and%20marginalised%20groups%20clustered%20in%20two%20ends%20of%20the%20occupational%20ladder%2C%20and%20horizontally%20%E2%80%93%20where%20dominant%20and%20marginalised%20groups%20have%20different%20tasks%20and%20differential%20wages%20within%20an%20occupation%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%20uses%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Duncan%20index%20which%20takes%20values%20between%200%20and%201%20where%200%20represents%20no%20segregation%20and%201%20represents%20complete%20segregation.%20The%20value%20of%20the%20index%20indicates%20the%20proportion%20of%20the%20workforce%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20reallocated%20between%20industries%20to%20achieve%20a%20state%20of%20no%20segregation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29155654%2Fimage-1364.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22958%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29155654%2Fimage-1364.png%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29155654%2Fimage-1364-300x75.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677528%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22240%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Duncan%20Index%2C%20industrial%20segregation%20is%20highest%20along%20gender%20lines%2C%20followed%20by%20caste%20and%20religion.%20Source%3A%20APU%20Report-Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20different%20social%20identities%20examined%20in%20the%20analysis%2C%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20industrial%20segregation%20in%20the%20Indian%20workforce%20was%20observed%20between%20men%20and%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20segregation%20index%20between%20men%20and%20women%20in%201983%20was%200.34%20which%20increased%20to%20reach%20a%20value%20of%200.41%20in%202021.%20Caste-based%20industrial%20segregation%20between%20SC%2FST%20and%20others%2C%20including%20OBCs%2C%20remained%20almost%20the%20same%2C%20declining%20slightly%20between%202004%20and%202021.%20Industrial%20segregation%20between%20Hindus%20and%20Muslim%20was%20even%20lower%20at%20around%200.17%20to%200.21.%20This%20means%20that%2040%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20would%20need%20to%20be%20redistributed%20along%20gender%20lines%20across%20industries%20to%20achieve%20gender%20parity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20post-reform%20era%20between%201993%20(0.35)%20and%202004%20(0.4)%20saw%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20growth%20in%20gender-based%20segregation%20across%20industries.%20However%2C%20throughout%20the%20course%20of%20the%20past%20four%20decades%2C%20women%20have%20consistently%20outnumbered%20males%20in%20a%20number%20of%20industries%2C%20such%20as%20in%20the%20production%20of%20tobacco%20products%2C%20domestic%20work%20(maids%2C%20etc.)%2C%20health%20and%20social%20work%2C%20education%2C%20and%20textile%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%20experiencing%20a%20modest%20decline%20by%202021%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20the%20tobacco%20sector%20reached%20its%20peak%20in%202017%2C%20surpassing%20five%20times%20their%20representation%20in%20the%20overall%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20over-representation%20of%20women%20in%20the%20waste%20management%20and%20sewerage%20sector%20has%20decreased%2C%20nevertheless%2C%20from%20an%20index%20value%20of%202.4%20in%201983%20to%201.2%20in%202021%2C%20which%20is%20a%20positive%20development.%20Caste-based%20industrial%20segregation%20between%20SC%2FST%20and%20others%2C%20including%20OBCs%2C%20remained%20constant%20at%20a%20Duncan%20index%20value%20of%200.23%20in%201983%20and%202021%2C%20with%20marginal%20changes%20in%20the%20years%20in%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20from%20the%20Scheduled%20Caste%20community%20have%20remained%20consistently%20over-represented%20in%20waste-management%20and%20sewerage%20and%20manufacture%20of%20leather%20and%20leather%20products.%20These%20two%20industries%20have%20strong%20historical%20ties%20with%20their%20caste%20identities.%20However%2C%20the%20extent%20of%20over-representation%20has%20declined%20substantially.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20the%20leather%20industry%2C%20the%20representation%20index%20declined%20from%204.6%20in%201983%20to%201.4%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20of%20waste%20management%20and%20sewerage%2C%20over-representation%20of%20SCs%20decreased%20from%20over%20five%20times%20their%20workforce%20share%20in%201983%20to%201.6%20times%20in%202011%2C%20with%20the%20largest%20drop%20occurring%20between%202004%20and%202011%2C%20which%20was%20also%20the%20high%20growth%20period.%20However%2C%20in%202017%2C%20it%20increased%20to%202.1%20and%20has%20remained%20above%20twice%20their%20workforce%20share%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20industrial%20segregation%20between%20Muslims%20and%20Hindus%20is%20relatively%20less-pronounced%20than%20gender%20and%20caste-based%20segregation%20and%20it%20has%20also%20declined%20over%20time.%20The%20segregation%20index%20declined%20from%20a%20peak%20of%200.22%20in%201993%20to%200.17%20in%202021.%20Among%20industries%20in%20which%20Muslims%20are%20consistently%20over-represented%20since%201983%2C%20their%20over-representation%20was%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20manufacture%20of%20tobacco%2C%20garments%2C%20and%20textiles%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEntrepreneurship%20and%20caste%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20interesting%20to%20see%20how%20the%20APU%20study%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2F%5C%22%3Ehighlighted%20the%20disparity%20among%20different%20castes%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20ownership%20of%20enterprises%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPeople%20belonging%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Caste%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20communities%20own%20very%20few%20enterprises%20as%20compared%20to%20their%20share%20in%20the%20population%20in%20urban%20and%20rural%20areas.%20A%20wage%20gap%20exists%20between%20people%20belonging%20to%20the%20general%20category%20and%20others%20much%20like%20the%20gap%20between%20men%20and%20women.%20This%20has%20also%20been%20seen%20in%20the%20case%20of%20MSMEs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ctable%20width%3D%5C%22624%5C%22%3E%20%3Ctbody%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3ESocial%20Groups%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%223%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22267%5C%22%3EShare%20in%20Workforce%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%223%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22267%5C%22%3EShare%20in%20enterprise%20Ownership%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E1998%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E2005%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E2013%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E1998%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E2005%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E2013%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3EST%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E10.7%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E10%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2289%5C%22%3E10.1%3C%2Ftd%