in%20of%20the%20dengue%20virus.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPatients%20from%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20rural%20areas%2C%20where%20WHO%20chief%20Tedros%20Adhanom%20Ghebreyesus%20said%20dengue%20cases%20were%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20have%20sought%20treatment%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20capital%20Dhaka%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F09%2F25%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fbangladesh-dengue-fever-outbreak.html%5C%22%3Ethe%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20its%20hospitals%20are%20already%20overwhelmed%2C%20its%20report%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20city%20is%20especially%20at%20risk%20of%20dengue%20transmission%20due%20to%20its%20high%20population%20and%20strained%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDhaka%20is%20densely%20populated%2C%20with%20many%20of%20its%2012%20million%20residents%20living%20in%20slums%2C%20where%20sanitation%20is%20poor.%20Clogged%20drainage%20systems%20store%20copious%20amounts%20of%20standing%20water%2C%20an%20optimal%20breeding%20ground%20for%20mosquitoes%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENYT%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20report%20said%20that%20hospitals%20in%20the%20capital%20city%20were%20running%20short%20of%20intravenous%20fluids%2C%20which%20are%20crucial%20to%20treat%20dengue%20patients%20as%20they%20often%20suffer%20from%20dehydration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnadolu%20Agency%20reported%20that%20government%20officials%20issued%20an%20order%20last%20week%20asking%20hospitals%20from%20outside%20Dhaka%20not%20to%20send%20patients%20to%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENYT%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20the%20disease%20has%20also%20spread%20to%20Rohingya%20camps%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20southeast%20%E2%80%93%20near%20its%20border%20with%20Myanmar%20%E2%80%93%20where%20over%2015%2C000%20cases%20were%20reported%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695997809000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22