ment%20in%20Bihar%20with%20its%20alliance%20partner%20JD(U)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20Lalu%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20intervening%20in%20the%20matter%20and%20defending%20Manoj%20Jha%2C%20the%20RJD%20and%20JDU%20leaders%20belonging%20to%20the%20Rajput%20community%20will%20read%20between%20the%20lines%20now%20and%20understand%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20game%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20senior%20RJD%20leader.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20opposition%20leaders%20should%20be%20cautious%20with%20the%20BJP%20which%20has%20mastered%20the%20art%20of%20diverting%20attention%20from%20its%20failure.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Framesh-bidhuri-has-exposed-the-real-face-of-the-bjp-beyond-pr-charm-offensives-studied-silences%5C%22%3ERamesh%20Bidhuri%20Has%20Exposed%20the%20Real%20Face%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20Beyond%20PR%20Charm%20Offensives%2C%20Studied%20Silences%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%20BJP%20leaders%2C%20some%20RJD%20and%20JD(U)%20leaders%20have%20also%20lashed%20out%20at%20Jha.%20Chetan%20Anand%2C%20RJD%20MLA%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20people%2C%20where%20he%20lives%2C%20get%20to%20hear%20this%20(poem)%2C%20they%20will%20not%20let%20him%20come%20there%E2%80%A6.%20I%20am%20shocked%20that%20people%20there%20(Rajya%20Sabha)%20listened%20to%20it.%20I%20would%20have%20protested%20then%20and%20there%20had%20I%20been%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chetan%20said.%20Chetan%20is%20the%20son%20of%20strongman%20Anand%20Mohan%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20recently%20released%20from%20jail%20after%20serving%20a%20prison%20term%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20murder%20of%20an%20Indian%20Administrative%20Service%20(IAS)%20officer%20in%20the%201990s.%20Anand%20Mohan%20also%20hit%20out%20at%20Jha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESanjay%20Singh%2C%20JD(U)%20leader%20and%20MLC%2C%20also%20criticised%20Jha.%20%E2%80%9CSuch%20statements%20create%20division%20in%20the%20society.%20We%20are%20with%20Nitish%20Kumar%20who%20unites%20people%20from%20all%20religions%20and%20castes.%20Manoj%20Jha%20will%20get%20a%20befitting%20reply%20for%20this.%20This%20is%20an%20indecent%20statement.%20He%20should%20apologise%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sanjay%20Singh%2C%20who%20hails%20from%20the%20Rajput%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98BJP%E2%80%99s%20trap%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20criticism%20that%20young%20leaders%20from%20RJD%20and%20JD(U)%20are%20falling%20into%20%E2%80%9CBJP%E2%80%99s%20trap%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20issue%20while%20also%20reflecting%20their%20lack%20of%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201931%2C%20Munshi%20Premchand%20wrote%20a%20short%20story%20titled%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EThakur%20ka%20Kuan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Through%20the%20characters%20of%20Gangi%20and%20her%20ailing%20husband%20Jokhu%20%E2%80%93%20the%20couple%20hailing%20from%20the%20untouchable%20community%20%E2%80%93%20the%20great%20storyteller%20commented%20on%20the%20stranglehold%20of%20a%20feudal%20lord%20on%20the%20means%20of%20livelihood%20in%20a%20village.%20Gangi%20is%20unable%20to%20draw%20water%20from%20a%20well%20belonging%20to%20a%20Thakur%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20ailing%20for%20long%2C%20is%20compelled%20to%20drink%20contaminated%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOmprakash%20Valmiki%E2%80%99s%20poem%2C%20%E2%80%98Thakur%20ka%20Kuan%E2%80%99%20can%20be%20said%20to%20be%20a%20follow-up%20on%20Premchand%E2%80%99s%20story%20on%20the%20exploitation%20of%20the%20Dalit%20communities%20and%20disproportionate%20control%20of%20the%20feudal%20classes%20on%20the%20means%20of%20livelihood%20in%20the%20rural%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20criticism%20that%20the%20current%20crop%20of%20RJD%20and%20JD(U)%20leaders%20lack%20the%20understanding%20that%20the%20second-generation%20socialist%20leaders%2C%20including%20Nitish%20Kumar%2C%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%2C%20and%20Shivanand%20Tiwary%2C%20possess.%20Nitish%20was%20known%20for%20his%20reading%20habit%20when%20he%20was%20a%20student%20leader.%20He%20is%20said%20to%20have%20read%20the%20complete%20writings%20of%20socialist%20icons%20Ram%20Manohar%20Lohia%2C%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Lalu%20Yadav%20was%20not%20very%20studious%2C%20he%20gained%20an%20immense%20understanding%20of%20society%20as%20he%20was%20under%20the%20tutelage%20of%20Lohia%2C%20Narayan%2C%20Karpoori%20Thakuri%2C%20and%20others.%20He%20also%20took%20an%20active%20part%20in%20the%20movements%20at%20the%20grassroots%20level%20meant%20to%20free%20deprived%20sections%20from%20oppression.%20Lalu%20began%20his%20political%20career%20by%20taking%20part%20in%20the%20procession%20led%20by%20Shivanand%20Tiwary%20against%20Shankaracharya%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20the%20Dalits%20in%20the%20late%201960s.%20Tiwary%20is%20known%20to%20read%20and%20write%20regularly%20till%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Lalu%20defended%20Jha%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20launching%20the%20book%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ESansad%20se%20Sadak%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20authored%20by%20Shivanand%20Tiwary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENalin%20Verma%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%2C%20author%2C%20media%20educator%2C%20and%20independent%20researcher%20in%20folklore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695994229000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29183927%2FThe-Wire-23.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthakur-poem-is-bjps-attack-on-manoj-jha-a-ploy-to-deflect-attention-from-ramesh-bidhuri%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20RJD%20MP's%20use%20of%20'Thakur%20ka%20Kuan'%20poem%20in%20his%20parliament%20speech%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20barrage%20of%20criticism%20from%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20described%20his%20comments%20as%20'anti-Rajput'.%20A%20BJP%20MLA%20from%20Bihar%20has%20threatened%20to%20behead%20Jha.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthakur-poem-is-bjps-attack-on-manoj-jha-a-ploy-to-deflect-attention-from-ramesh-bidhuri%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%20%7C%20Does%20India%20Have%20a%20Colonial%20Consitituion%20Or%20is%20That%20a%20Mistaken%20View%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29181817%2Fmaxresdefault.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20discuss%20his%20new%20book%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Colonial%20Constitution%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Arghya%20Sengupta%20explains%20why%20he%20believes%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20is%20colonial%20and%20responds%20to%20a%20series%20of%20questions%20challenging%20his%20view%20and%20also%20the%20arguments%20upon%20which%20it%20is%20based.%20In%20a%2045-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Sengupta%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20director%2C%20Vidhi%20Centre%20for%20Legal%20Policy%20%E2%80%93%20is%20questioned%20about%20his%20two%20broad%20reasons%20for%20believing%20the%20constitution%20is%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20he%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Constitution%20of%20India%20is%20a%20colonial%20document.%20It%E2%80%99s%20colonial%20for%20the%20simple%20factual%20reason%20that%20it%20is%20heavily%20borrowed%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%2C%201935%2C%20a%20fact%20that%20has%20been%20widely%20glossed%20over.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20he%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20Constitution%20is%20colonial%20in%20a%20more%20conceptual%20sense%3A%20it%20sets%20up%20a%20government%20that%20towers%20over%20the%20citizen%20much%20like%20colonial%20governments%20tend%20to%20do.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20discussion%20centres%20around%20the%20constitution%2C%20its%20origin%2C%20its%20character%2C%20the%20structure%20it%20adopted%20as%20well%20as%20the%20possible%20structures%20it%20avoided.%20Watch%20the%20video%20for%20complete%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FgtXTk8Zs-ns%3Fsi%3D3GgQqRO1NYbg9UZf%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695992443000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29181817%2Fmaxresdefault.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-does-india-have-a-colonial-consitituion-or-is-that-a-mistaken-view%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Arghya%20Sengupta%20explains%20why%20he%20believes%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20is%20colonial%20and%20responds%20to%20a%20series%20of%20questions%20challenging%20his%20view%20and%20also%20the%20arguments%20upon%20which%20it%20is%20based.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-does-india-have-a-colonial-consitituion-or-is-that-a-mistaken-view%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Women%20of%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20in%20a%20two-part%20series%20by%20the%20author%20on%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20Bill.%20Read%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fbetween-history-and-histrionics%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi-led%20government%20may%20have%20been%20under%20its%20own%20compulsions%20to%20adopt%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20Bill%20with%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20next%20elections%20but%20the%20discussion%20on%20the%20need%20for%20reservations%20for%20women%20has%20a%20long%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20is%20well-known%2C%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20and%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20women%20members%20vociferously%20argued%20against%20reservation%20with%20former%20Lok%20Sabha%20member%20Renuka%20Ray%20decisively%20stating%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cwhen%20there%20is%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%2C%20the%20question%20of%20their%20consideration%20for%20general%20seats%2C%20however%20competent%20they%20may%20be%2C%20does%20not%20usually%20arise.%20We%20feel%20that%20women%20will%20get%20more%20chances%20if%20the%20consideration%20is%20of%20ability%20alone.%E2%80%9D%20Reservation%2C%20she%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Floksabha.nic.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Fcadebatefiles%2FC18071947.html%2520accessed%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eargued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20would%20be%20%E2%80%98an%20impediment%20to%20our%20growth%20and%20an%20insult%20to%20our%20very%20intelligence%20and%20capacity.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20128%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20contextualise%20the%20shift%20in%20the%20debate%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement%20in%20the%20post-independence%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20in%201974%20that%20the%20Committee%20on%20the%20Status%20of%20Women%20in%20India%20undertook%20the%20most%20comprehensive%20review%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20status%20since%20independence.%20The%20report%20made%20a%20specific%20note%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdifficulties%20being%20experienced%20by%20women%20in%20obtaining%20adequate%20representation%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdeclining%20trend%20in%20the%20number%20of%20women%20legislators%E2%80%9D%20which%20may%20result%20in%20women%20%E2%80%9Closing%20faith%20in%20the%20political%20process%20to%20change%20their%20conditions%20in%20life%2C%20%5Band%5D%20may%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20political%20system%20and%20become%20either%20passive%20partners%20or%20rebels.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%20the%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20chose%20not%20to%20recommend%20reservations%2C%20prompting%20two%20of%20its%20members%20to%20submit%20a%20dissent%20note.%20%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20note%2C%20professors%20Lotika%20Sarkar%20and%20Vina%20Mazumdar%20(the%20latter%20was%20also%20the%20member%20secretary%20of%20the%20committee)%20pointed%20out%20that%20despite%20never%20having%20been%20supporters%20of%20special%20representation%20or%20class%20representation%20in%20any%20form%2C%20they%20were%20compelled%20to%20confront%20the%20question%20and%20disagree%20with%20the%20majority%20view%20in%20the%20committee%20because%20%E2%80%9Ca%20political%20system%20cannot%20be%20based%20on%20ideology%20alone%20but%20must%20keep%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20actualities%20of%20the%20social%20situation%20and%20so%20adjust%20its%20operation%20as%20to%20achieve%20the%20desired%20goals%20of%20the%20society.%20The%20mechanics%20of%20the%20system%2C%20if%20they%20do%20not%20grapple%20with%20the%20needs%20of%20a%20society%2C%20can%20defeat%20the%20ultimate%20objective%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20It%20is%20for%20this%20reason%20that%20we%20are%20compelled%20to%20dissent%20from%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20decision%20on%20this%20point.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20observations%20facilitated%20a%20long%20term%20discussion%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20political%20bodies%20with%20special%20focus%20on%20local%20bodies.%20They%20drew%20on%20discussions%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20Panchayati%20Raj%20system%2C%20the%20principle%20of%20financial%20devolution%20as%20part%20of%20the%20governance%20to%20advance%20the%20principles%20of%20federalism%20and%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAshok%20Mehta%20Committee%20in%201977%2C%20these%20aspects%20were%20the%20subject%20of%20debate%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eseveral%20committees%20through%20the%201980s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fbetween-history-and-histrionics%5C%22%3EBetween%20History%20and%20Histrionics%2C%20the%20Nari%20Shakti%20Vandan%20Adhiniyam%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%20the%201980s%20saw%20discussion%20picking%20up%20on%20both%2C%20the%20aspect%20of%20participatory%20governance%20at%20the%20local%20level%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20women%20in%20these%20processes%20%E2%80%93%20the%20latter%20pointing%20to%20the%20dissonance%20between%20political%20institutions%20and%20the%20changing%20aspirations%20of%20women%20as%20articulated%20by%20the%20resurgent%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2064%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%20Bill%20of%201989%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20not%20be%20passed%20%E2%80%93%20reflected%20the%20disappointments%20as%20well%20as%20the%20contradictions%2C%20with%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement%20rejecting%20any%20attempt%20to%20be%20co-opted%20through%20a%20process%20of%20nominations%20to%20the%20local%20bodies.%20The%20making%20of%20the%2073%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and74%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%20go%20back%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20this%20history%20and%20the%20coalescence%20of%20diverse%20factors.%20These%20included%3A%20the%20ground%20observations%20after%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ereservations%20for%20women%20in%20the%20local%20bodies%20in%20Karnataka%20after%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20Zilla%20Parishad%2C%20Taluk%20Panchayat%20Samithis%2C%20Mandal%20Panchayats%20and%20Nyaya%20Panchayats%20Act%2C%201983%20which%20generated%20interest%20among%20women%20in%20local%20bodies.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eformer%20Prime%20Minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20wish%20to%20introduce%20reservation%20for%20women%20as%20an%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20owed%20the%20massive%20mandate%20he%20received%20in%201984%20to%20women%20voters%2C%20coupled%20with%20policy%20makers%20and%20bureaucrats%20following%20up%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20CSWI%20who%20were%20instrumental%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eensuring%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E73%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%2074%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Constitutional%20amendments%20for%2033%25%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%201992.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20all%20the%20cynicism%20surrounding%20discussions%20on%20the%20two%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amendments%20in%20the%20higher%20echelons%20of%20society%2C%20the%20enthusiasm%20it%20generated%20amongst%20the%20mass%20of%20women%20was%20visible%20and%20pushed%20the%20debate%20on%20reservations%20for%20women%20in%20the%20higher%20legislative%20bodies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20these%20were%20developments%20in%20official%20quarters%2C%20it%20was%20the%20movement%E2%80%99s%20experience%20of%20confronting%20women%E2%80%99s%20increased%20marginalisation%20that%20led%20to%20their%20engaging%20with%20the%20demand%20for%20increased%20representation%20through%20the%20legislative%20process.%20By%20the%201990s%20the%20challenge%20for%20women%20to%20assert%20their%20constitutional%20right%20to%20be%20elected%20was%20clearly%20visible%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20growing%20criminalisation%20and%20the%20use%20of%20muscle%20and%20money%20power%20in%20politics.%20It%20became%20even%20more%20glaring%20when%20electoral%20battles%20entered%20the%20phase%20of%20coalition%20politics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fin-charts-what-womens-representation-in-indias-parliament-assemblies-looks-like-now%5C%22%3EIn%20Charts%3A%20What%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Representation%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Parliament%2C%20Assemblies%20Looks%20Like%20Now%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20bureaucrat%20Nirmala%20Buch%2C%20who%20played%20no%20small%20part%20in%20ensuring%20the%20passage%20of%20these%20critical%20amendments%2C%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9CMyths%20were%20created%20about%20women%E2%80%99s%20disinterest%20and%20passivity%20in%20politics%2C%20and%20about%20how%20female%20relatives%20of%20influential%20politicians%20from%20the%20well-off%20sections%20merely%20occupied%20these%20seats%20while%20the%20men%20were%20the%20ones%20who%20actually%20carried%20out%20the%20tasks.%E2%80%9D%20She%20countered%20this%20with%20data%20that%20disproved%20these%20stories%20and%20documented%20the%20work%20of%20younger%2C%20first%20time%20women%20entrants%20from%20economically%20weaker%20sections%20and%20their%20participation%20and%20performance%20levels.%20She%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20challenge%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20patriarchy%20whereby%20the%20women%20are%20included%20but%20not%20allowed%20to%20participate%20and%20their%20work%20is%20consistently%20undervalued%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20women%20who%20contested%20the%20panchayat%20elections%20would%20not%20have%20been%20able%20to%20do%20so%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20reservations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20her%2C%20the%20failure%20to%20tackle%20issues%20of%20rotation%20and%20such%20matters%20reflected%20the%20lack%20of%20serious%20efforts%20to%20%E2%80%9Cresolve%20the%20issue%20of%20reservations%20in%20the%20national%20and%20state%20legislatures%20make%20it%20look%20like%20a%20tactic%20to%20divert%20attention%20from%20the%20impasse%20over%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201995%20women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20issued%20a%20clear%20statement%20that%20%E2%80%98women%E2%80%99s%20political%20participation%20needs%20to%20be%20encouraged%20by%20extending%20the%20present%20reservations%20in%20the%20panchayats%E2%80%99%20and%20demanded%20%E2%80%98at%20least%2033%25%20reservations%20in%20the%20State%20assemblies%20and%20Parliament.%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20issued%20by%20seven%20national%20organisations%3A%20the%20All%20India%20Democratic%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Association%20(AIDWA)%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Mahila%20Dakshata%20Samiti%20(AIMDS)%2C%20All%20India%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Conference%20(AIWC)%2C%20Centre%20for%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Development%20Studies%20(CWDS)%2C%20Joint%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Programme%20(JWP)%2C%20The%20National%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Women%20(NFIW)%2C%20Young%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Christian%20Association%20(YWCA)%2C%20with%2099%20other%20organisations%20from%20across%20India%20supporting%20the%201995%20Declaration%20of%20the%20National%20Convention%20of%20Women%20in%20Beijing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAhead%20of%20the%201996%20elections%2C%20these%20seven%20national%20organisations%20made%20a%20public%20appeal%20to%20national%20political%20parties%20asking%20for%20inclusion%20in%20their%20manifestos%20a%20commitment%20to%20make%20necessary%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%20to%20ensure%20a%20minimum%20of%20one%20third%20seats%20to%20assemblies%20and%20parliament%20for%20women%20immediately.%20Representatives%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20met%20leaders%20of%20all%20the%20national%20parties%2C%20pushing%20for%20a%20debate%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20receiving%20diverse%20responses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomens-reservation-bill-parliament%5C%22%3EThe%20State%2C%20Formally%2C%20Remains%20Male%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20following%20up%20on%20these%20interventions%20that%20the%20United%20Front%20government%20led%20by%20Deve%20Gowda%20in%201996%20introduced%20the%2081%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Est%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Constitution%20Amendment%20Bill%20for%2033%25%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20legislative%20bodies%2C%20steered%20by%20Pramila%20Dandavate.%20This%20Bill%20was%20referred%20to%20a%20Parliament%20Select%20Committee%2C%20popularly%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20Geeta%20Mukherjee%20Committee.%20Women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20followed%20up%20their%20efforts%20with%20a%20meeting%20and%20a%20memorandum%20to%20the%20committee%20in%20November%201996.%20The%20subsequent%20history%20of%20the%20various%20versions%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20well%20documented%2C%20including%20the%20reference%20to%20a%20second%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20on%20Law%20and%20Justice%20in%202008.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20not%20sufficiently%20recognised%20is%20the%20persistent%20efforts%20by%20the%20movement%20to%20gather%20support%20from%20different%20political%20parties.%20They%20engaged%20in%20continuous%20debate%20on%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20figure%20of%2033%25%20%E2%80%93%20considered%20necessary%20for%20a%20critical%20mass%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20question%20of%20quota%20within%20quota%2C%20proxies%20and%20debates%20arising%20from%20restrictions%20brought%20according%20to%20the%20two-child%20norm%20in%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Representation%20Act%20and%20their%20gender%20implications%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20backlash%20elected%20women%20faced%20for%20standing%20their%20ground%20in%20the%20local%20bodies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20have%2C%20over%20the%20last%20three%20decades%2C%20sustained%20a%20debate%20on%20all%20aspects%20and%20maintained%20that%20the%20Bill%20needs%20to%20be%20brought%20to%20parliament%20to%20allow%20for%20a%20constructive%20debate%20on%20all%20aspects.%20There%20is%20hardly%20any%20constitutional%20authority%20that%20the%20organisations%20did%20not%20approach%20in%20these%20decades%20to%20push%20for%20a%20debate%2C%20even%20as%20there%20was%20a%20raging%20debate%20within%20the%20movement%20with%20regard%20to%20quotas%20and%20clauses%20for%20sub-reservation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Let%20the%20debate%20happen%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20constant%20refrain%20from%20the%20movement%20even%20as%20parties%20scuttled%20this%20very%20debate%20in%20the%20name%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98lack%20of%20consensus.%E2%80%99%20The%20strength%20to%20persist%20with%20the%20demand%20has%20largely%20come%20from%20the%20enthusiasm%20amongst%20the%20mass%20of%20women%20based%20on%20the%20experiences%20of%20working%20with%20the%2073%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E-74%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amendments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20these%20women%20who%20have%20carried%20the%20campaign%2C%20asserting%20democracy%20at%20the%20grassroots%2C%20facing%20the%20wrath%20of%20vested%20interests%20all%20across%20different%20states%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20cynicism%20surrounding%20the%20dismissive%20references%20to%20proxies%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3Epanch%20patis%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20term%20coined%20for%20husbands%20of%20elected%20leaders)%20%3Cspan%3Ein%20the%20upper%20echelons.%20These%20years%20have%20seen%20a%20movement%20on%20the%20ground%20as%20well%20as%20a%20petition%20in%20the%20court%20in%202011%20for%20implementation%20of%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A033%25%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20urban%20local%20bodies%20in%20Nagaland%20after%20the%20state%20government%20opposed%20implementation%20and%20application%20of%20the%20law%20citing%20customary%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20as%20the%20debate%20goes%20on%20about%20the%20need%20for%20mechanisms%20to%20make%20the%20legislation%20inclusive%20in%20terms%20of%20women%20from%20specifically%20marginalised%20groups%20and%20communities%2C%20it%20may%20be%20worthwhile%20to%20recall%20what%20the%20two%20pioneers%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20studies%20in%20India%2C%20Sarkar%20and%20Mazumdar%2C%20pointed%20out%20in%20their%20dissent%20note%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20one%20applies%20the%20principle%20of%20democracy%20to%20a%20society%20characterised%20by%20tremendous%20inequalities%2C%20such%20special%20protections%20are%20only%20spearheads%20to%20pierce%20through%20the%20barriers%20of%20inequality.%20An%20unattainable%20goal%20is%20as%20meaningless%20as%20a%20right%20that%20cannot%20be%20exercised.%20Equality%20of%20opportunities%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20tremendous%20disabilities%20and%20obstacles%20which%20the%20social%20system%20imposes%20on%20all%20those%20sections%20whom%20traditional%20India%20treated%20as%20second%20class%20or%20even%20third%20class%20citizens.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EIndu%20Agnihotri%20is%20a%20retired%20professor%20and%20former%20director%20of%20Centre%20for%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Development%20Studies%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695992417000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20women%20who%20carried%20the%20campaign%2C%20asserting%20democracy%20at%20the%20grassroots%20and%20faced%20the%20wrath%20of%20vested%20interest%20across%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Longest-serving%20US%20female%20senator%20dies%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A16959919