mpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-to-spin-off-list-6-companies-to-attract-big-ticket-investment-123092900794_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22M.S.%20Swaminathan%20Will%20Forever%20Be%20Remembered%20in%20the%20Hearts%20of%20Millions%20of%20Farmers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29170658%2Fmss-swaminathan.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20are%20a%20few%20words%20of%20English%20that%20almost%20every%20Indian%20farmer%20would%20know%2C%20those%20would%20be%20%E2%80%98Swaminathan%20Report%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98Swaminathan%20Commission%20Report.%E2%80%99%20They%20also%20know%20what%20for%20them%20is%20its%20main%20recommendation%3A%20Minimum%20Support%20Price%20%3D%20Comprehensive%20Cost%20of%20Production%20%2B%2050%25%20(also%20known%20as%20C2%2B50%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProfessor%20M.S.%20Swaminathan%20will%20be%20remembered%20not%20merely%20in%20the%20halls%20of%20government%20and%20bureaucracy%2C%20or%20even%20the%20institutions%20of%20science%20%E2%80%93%20but%20mainly%20in%20the%20hearts%20of%20millions%20of%20peasants%20demanding%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Report%20of%20the%20National%20Commission%20for%20Farmers%20(NCF).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndian%20farmers%2C%20though%2C%20simply%20call%20it%20the%20Swaminathan%20Report%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20the%20huge%20input%2C%20impact%20and%20indelible%20imprint%20he%20made%20on%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20NCF%2C%20of%20which%20he%20was%20chairman.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20reports%20is%20one%20of%20betrayal%20and%20suppression%20by%20both%20the%20UPA%20and%20NDA%20governments.%20The%20first%20of%20the%20reports%20was%20submitted%20in%20December%202004%2C%20the%20fifth%20and%20final%20one%20around%20October%202006.%20Let%20alone%20a%20special%20session%20of%20parliament%20on%20the%20agrarian%20crisis%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20we%20desperately%20need%20%E2%80%93%20not%20even%20an%20hour%E2%80%99s%20dedicated%20discussion%20was%20ever%20held.%20And%20it%20is%20now%2019%20years%20since%20the%20first%20report%20was%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20came%20to%20power%2C%20to%20some%20degree%20aided%20by%20a%20promise%20they%20made%20of%20speedily%20implementing%20the%20Swaminathan%20Report%2C%20especially%20its%20MSP%20formula%20recommendation.%20Instead%2C%20the%20incoming%20government%20speedily%20filed%20an%20affidavit%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20saying%20that%20would%20not%20be%20feasible%20as%20it%20would%20distort%20market%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20reasoning%20of%20the%20UPA%20and%20NDA%20was%20that%20the%20reports%20were%20too%20%E2%80%9Cpro-farmer%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20both%20governments%20were%20trying%20to%20hand%20over%20Indian%20farming%20to%20the%20corporate%20sector.%20The%20report%20was%20the%20first%20thing%20approaching%20a%20positive%20blueprint%20for%20agriculture%20since%20Independence.%20Helmed%20by%20a%20man%20who%20sought%20an%20entirely%20different%20framework%3A%20that%20we%20measure%20growth%20in%20agriculture%20in%20terms%20of%20growth%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%2C%20not%20merely%20in%20increased%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPersonally%2C%20the%20abiding%20memory%20I%20have%20of%20him%20goes%20back%20to%202005%2C%20when%20he%20was%20NCF%20chairperson%2C%20and%20I%20appealed%20to%20him%20to%20visit%20Vidarbha.%20Farmer%20suicides%20in%20the%20region%20were%20then%20occurring%20at%20the%20rate%20of%206-8%20a%20day%20in%20some%20seasons.%20Things%20were%20as%20miserable%20as%20they%20could%20be%2C%20though%20you%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20learn%20that%20from%20most%20of%20your%20media.%20(In%202006%2C%20we%20counted%20just%20six%20journalists%20from%20outside%20Vidarbha%20who%20were%20covering%20what%20was%20perhaps%20the%20largest%20wave%20of%20suicides%20in%20recorded%20history%20in%20the%20six%20worst-hit%20districts%20of%20the%20region.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Lakme%20Fashion%20Week%20in%20Mumbai%20was%20being%20covered%20by%20512%20accredited%20journalists%20and%20about%20100%20more%20on%20daily%20passes.%20The%20Fashion%20Week%E2%80%99s%20theme%20ironically%2C%20was%20cotton%20%E2%80%93%20elegantly%20presented%20on%20the%20ramp%20while%20men%2C%20women%20and%20children%20who%20grew%20that%20cotton%20were%20taking%20their%20lives%20in%20unprecedented%20numbers%20an%20hour%E2%80%99s%20flight%20away.)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20to%202005.%20Prof%20Swaminathan%20responded%20to%20that%20appeal%20from%20us%20journalists%20covering%20Vidarbha%20much%20faster%20than%20any%20of%20us%20had%20expected%20and%20arrived%20there%20very%20soon%20after%20with%20an%20NCF%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Vilasrao%20Deshmukh%20government%20was%20alarmed%20by%20his%20visit%20and%20tried%20their%20best%20to%20give%20him%20a%20guided%20tour%20which%20would%20keep%20him%20in%20many%20discussions%20with%20bureaucrats%20and%20technocrats%2C%20ceremonies%20at%20agricultural%20colleges%2C%20and%20more.%20The%20soul%20of%20politeness%2C%20he%20told%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%20he%20would%20visit%20the%20places%20they%20wished%20him%20to%20%E2%80%93%20but%20that%20he%20would%20also%20spend%20time%20in%20the%20field%20at%20the%20places%20I%20asked%20him%20to%20go%20to%20along%20with%20me%20and%20fellow%20journalists%20like%20Jaideep%20Hardikar.%3Cbr%3E%20And%20he%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Wardha%2C%20we%20took%20him%20to%20the%20house%20of%20Shyamrao%20Khatale%2C%20whose%20sons%2C%20the%20working%20farmers%20in%20the%20household%2C%20had%20taken%20their%20own%20lives.%20We%20arrived%20to%20find%20that%20Shyamrao%20had%20passed%20away%20a%20few%20hours%20earlier%20%E2%80%93%20of%20ill%20health%2C%20exacerbated%20by%20hunger%2C%20and%20unable%20to%20cope%20with%20the%20loss%20of%20his%20sons.%20The%20state%20government%20tried%20to%20amend%20the%20route%20saying%20the%20man%20was%20dead.%20Swaminathan%20insisted%20he%20would%20visit%20to%20pay%20his%20respects%20and%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20next%20few%20house%20visits%2C%20he%20was%20in%20tears%20listening%20to%20the%20families%20of%20those%20who%20had%20ended%20their%20own%20lives.%20He%20also%20attended%20a%20memorable%20gathering%20of%20distressed%20farmers%20in%20Waifad%2C%20Wardha%2C%20organised%20by%20the%20redoubtable%20Vijay%20Jawandhia%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20our%20finest%20intellectuals%20on%20matters%20agrarian.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20an%20elderly%20farmer%20in%20the%20crowd%20stood%20up%20and%20asked%20him%20angrily%20why%20the%20government%20hated%20them%20so%20much.%20Should%20we%20become%20terrorists%20to%20be%20heard%3F%20The%20professor%2C%20deeply%20pained%2C%20addressed%20him%20and%20his%20friends%20with%20great%20patience%20and%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESwaminathan%20was%20already%20in%20his%2080s.%20I%20marvelled%20at%20his%20stamina%2C%20calm%20and%20graciousness.%20We%20also%20observed%20how%20sincerely%20he%20would%20engage%20with%20people%20who%20were%20strongly%20critical%20of%20his%20opinions%20and%20work.%20How%20patiently%20he%20would%20listen%20%E2%80%93%20and%20even%20concede%20%E2%80%93%20to%20some%20of%20their%20criticisms.%20No%20one%20else%20I%20knew%20would%20so%20readily%20invite%20his%20critics%20to%20a%20seminar%20or%20workshop%20he%20was%20organising%20to%20say%20publicly%20the%20things%20they%20had%20told%20him%20personally.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20surely%20one%20of%20the%20most%20impressive%20characteristics%20of%20the%20man%20that%20he%20could%20look%20back%20over%20decades%20and%20address%20what%20he%20now%20saw%20as%20the%20failures%20and%20shortcomings%20in%20his%20own%20work.%20He%20was%20shocked%2C%20and%20said%20so%2C%20by%20the%20way%20and%20the%20scale%20at%20which%20the%20use%20of%20chemical%20fertilisers%20and%20pesticides%20went%20so%20wildly%20out%20of%20control%20with%20the%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20something%20he%20had%20not%20envisaged%20or%20imagined.%20Over%20decades%2C%20he%20grew%20more%20and%20more%20sensitive%20to%20ecology%20and%20environment%2C%20to%20the%20use%20and%20abuse%20of%20water%20resources.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20he%20also%20grew%20increasingly%20critical%20of%20the%20unregulated%2C%20reckless%20spread%20of%20Bt%20or%20genetically%20modified%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20passing%20of%20Mankombu%20Sambasivan%20Swaminathan%2C%20India%20has%20lost%20not%20just%20its%20foremost%20agricultural%20scientist%2C%20but%20a%20great%20mind%20and%20a%20fine%20human%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fp-sainath%5C%22%3EP.%20Sainath%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20founder%20and%20editor%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ruralindiaonline.org%2F%5C%22%3EPeople%E2%80%99s%20Archive%20of%20Rural%20India.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695987797000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29170658%2Fmss-swaminathan.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fms-swaminathan-obituary-p-sainath%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Through%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20National%20Commission%20for%20Farmers%2C%20the%20agricultural%20scientists%20proposed%20that%20we%20measure%20growth%20in%20agriculture%20in%20terms%20of%20growth%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%20and%20not%20merely%20increased%20output.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fms-swaminathan-obituary-p-sainath%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22If%20There%20Was%20Political%20Will%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Raging%20Cost%20of%20Living%20Crisis%20Could%20Be%20Eased%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29155126%2Frickshaw-2158447_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20the%20fourth%20in%20a%20series%20on%20the%20state%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%20co-curated%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Financial%20Accountability%2C%20New%20Delhi%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E.%20Read%20the%20first%20article%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fdoubling-farmers-income-a-tale-of-empty-promises-deceit-and-propaganda%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20the%20second%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fis-the-pandemic-really-over-unearthing-stories-of-death-debt-and-distress%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20the%20third%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fnarendra-modis-decade-in-power-has-brought-a-shrinking-welfare-landscape-to-india%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CScience%20of%20producing%20unreliable%20facts%20from%20reliable%20figures%E2%80%9D%3A%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20Evan%20Esar%2C%20an%20American%20humorist%2C%20had%20to%20say%20about%20statistics.%20One%20can%20identify%20with%20the%20frustration.%20For%20a%20lay%20person%2C%20often%20it%20becomes%20difficult%20to%20fathom%20where%20we%20are%20really%20headed%20as%20an%20economy.%20Are%20there%20green%20shoots%20or%20dry%20roots%3F%20Statistics%20are%20often%20perplexing.%20The%20reassurances%20from%20the%20finance%20ministry%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20stand%20the%20simple%20test%20of%20vegetable%20or%20grocery%20shopping%20in%20the%20bazaar.%20Is%20there%20a%20recovery%3F%20Whose%20recovery%3F%20At%20what%20cost%3F%20Who%20is%20paying%20the%20cost%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20for%20illustration%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20the%20graph%20below%20(Figure%20A).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143354%2FCLC1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22936%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143354%2FCLC1.png%20936w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143354%2FCLC1-300x171.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22532%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20A.%20Consumer%20Confidence%20Index%20Sep%202021%20%E2%80%93%20Jul%202023.%20Source%3A%20RBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%20will%20see%20is%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20consumer%20confidence%20(current%20situation)%20index.%20It%20is%20supposed%20to%20give%20a%20sense%20as%20to%20how%20optimistic%20or%20pessimistic%20consumers%20are%20regarding%20their%20expected%20financial%20situation%20and%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economic%20condition.%20Consumer%20optimism%20indicates%20they%20will%20spend%20more%20and%20stimulate%20the%20economy.%20Consumer%20pessimism%20can%20lead%20to%20postponing%20spending%20and%20thus%20stagnation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20graph%20above%2C%20it%20does%20look%20as%20if%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20things%20are%20getting%20back%20into%20shape%20%E2%80%93%20a%20nice%20linear%20projection%20trend%20that%20will%20validate%20the%20claims%20of%20the%20government.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20thing%20with%20statistics%2C%20they%20can%20hide%20more%20than%20they%20reveal%20unless%20we%20clarify%20our%20reference%20points%20and%20ask%20a%20few%20probing%20questions.%20In%20this%20instance%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20just%20zoom%20out%20and%20see%20the%20picture%20below%20(Figure%20B).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143545%2FCLC2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22984%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143545%2FCLC2.png%20984w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143545%2FCLC2-300x173.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677501%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22568%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20B.%20Consumer%20Confidence%20Index%20Mar%202015%20%E2%80%93%20Mar%202023.%20Source%3A%20RBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EVoila!%20The%20optimism%20disappears.%20The%20linear%20trend%20projection%20seems%20to%20be%20only%20an%20optical%20illusion%20created%20by%20the%20preceding%20sharp%20dip%20caused%20by%20the%20pandemic%20and%20harsh%20lockdowns.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20really%20need%20a%20graph%20to%20validate%20that%20people%20are%20buying%20relatively%20more%20than%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20lockdowns%20and%20deaths.%20So%20Figure%20A%20hardly%20merits%20celebration.%20It%20is%20Figure%20B%20that%20is%20more%20important%20and%20worrying.%20It%20is%20also%20probably%20the%20only%20phenomenon%20under%20the%20present%20government%20that%20can%20be%20characterised%20by%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Csecular%E2%80%9D.%20As%20it%20shows%20that%20the%20general%20trend%20has%20been%20a%20secular%20fall%20from%202015%20onwards%20(see%20the%20trend%20line).%20It%20is%20symptomatic%20of%20the%20slump%20in%20demand%20that%20in%20fact%20preceded%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20results%20of%20the%20consumer%20confidence%20survey%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frbidocs.rbi.org.in%2Frdocs%2FPublications%2FPDFs%2FCCSJULY2023958360FCB15447479F69824DB1D1D6A7.PDF%5C%22%3ERBI%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20fact%20shows%20that%20the%20current%20situation%20index%20has%20dipped%20again%20in%20July%202023%20and%20is%20a%20shade%20lower%20than%20the%20previous%20survey.%20Overall%2C%20it%20shows%20a%20downward%20slippage%20from%20108.6%20points%20in%20the%20round%20of%20March%202015%20to%2088.1%20points%20in%20July%202023.%20The%20declaration%20of%20Amrit%20Kaal%20from%20the%20Red%20Fort%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20given%20much%20confidence%20to%20the%20citizens.%20As%20far%20as%20future%20expectations%20are%20concerned%2C%20except%20for%20the%20grim%20outlook%20about%20prices%2C%20the%20survey%20otherwise%20shows%20a%20marginal%20positivity.%20But%20again%20if%20one%20zooms%20out%2C%20the%20future%20expectation%20index%20has%20in%20fact%20slid%20down%20from%20126.7%20in%20March%202015%20to%20116.6%20in%20July%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20beast%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20retail%20inflation%20remains%20high%20at%206.83%25%20in%20August%202023%20after%20a%2015-month%20high%20of%207.44%25%20in%20July.%20What%20may%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20slight%20dent%20needs%20to%20be%20qualified%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20on%20top%20of%20an%20already%20high%20base%20of%20August%202022.%20There%20has%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20inflation%20rate%20of%20fuel%20and%20light%20segment%20from%203.67%25%20to%204.31%25%20which%20remains%20worrying.%20What%20the%20numbers%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20end%20up%20conveying%20are%20the%20social%20implications%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis%20and%20the%20ways%20of%20coping%20the%20poor%20are%20forced%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20supply%20cuts%20by%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20other%20OPEC%2B%20nations%20have%20pushed%20up%20fuel%20prices%20at%20an%20astonishing%20pace%20which%20was%20closely%20followed%20by%20a%20rising%20tide%20of%20food%20price%20inflation.%20Added%20to%20this%20was%20the%20continued%20levy%20of%20astronomical%20taxes%20on%20fuels%20at%20retail%20outlets%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%20The%20unorganised%20sector%20in%20particular%20(that%20employs%20nearly%2085%25%20of%20workers)%20where%20wages%20are%20never%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%2C%20has%20suffered%20the%20brunt%2C%20its%20back%20being%20broken%20by%20the%20successive%20shocks%20of%20demonetisation%2C%20GST%20and%20finally%20the%20sudden%20and%20harsh%20lockdowns.%20In%20FY%202022-23%2C%20the%20gross%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Fmint-explainer-how-inflation-is-hurting-indias-household-financial-savings-11695124010070.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSummary%26amp%3Btext%3DIndia%2527s%2520%2520household%2520%2520savings%2520have%2520%2520touched%2CFY21%2520to%25207.2%2525%2520in%2520FY22%5C%22%3Esavings%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Indian%20households%20stood%20at%205.1%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20the%20lowest%20in%20at%20least%2023%20years.%20While%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20work%20and%20incomes%20that%20ate%20into%20the%20meagre%20savings%20of%20the%20poor%2C%20by%20the%20time%20they%20were%20hoping%20to%20recover%2C%20the%20steep%20rise%20in%20prices%20has%20once%20again%20been%20further%20depleting%20their%20savings%20as%20incomes%20have%20hardly%20been%20able%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20while%20the%20wages%20of%20construction%20workers%20and%20agricultural%20workers%20have%20increased%20by%20only%2010.5%25%20and%2012%25%20respectively%20in%20rural%20India%20from%20April%202021%20to%20March%202023%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20cereals%20have%20increased%20by%20a%20whopping%2022%25.%20Add%20to%20it%20the%20fuel%20segment%20of%20the%20index%20that%20has%20increased%20by%2016%25%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20milk%20and%20milk%20products%20that%20has%20increased%20by%2014%25.%20Higher%20price%20prevailing%20in%20the%20retail%20market%20effectively%20shrinks%20the%20disposable%20income%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20people%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20acts%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Fmagazine%2Fdeep-dive%2Fstory%2Fbattered-by-inflation-and-faltering-demand-indias-consumer-goods-industry-is-ailing-399174-2023-09-21%5C%22%3Edampener%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20demand%20for%20consumer%20products%20as%20people%20postpone%20non-essential%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFigure%20C%20below%20shows%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20wages%20of%20construction%20workers%20as%20compared%20to%20fuel%20prices%2C%20and%20food%20and%20beverages%20prices%20in%20rural%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29151157%2FCLC3.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22979%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29151157%2FCLC3.png%20979w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29151157%2FCLC3-300x166.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677511%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22543%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20C%3A%20Annual%20Variation%3A%20CPI%20%E2%80%93%20R%20across%20(food%20%26amp%3B%20beverages%20%26amp%3B%20Fuel%20%26amp%3B%20Light)%20and%20Rural%20Wage%20Rate.%3Cbr%3ENote%3A%20Annual%20Variation%20is%20computed%20by%20taking%20the%20annual%20average%20of%20months%20in%20a%20FY%20%26amp%3B%20annual%20avg.%20of%20monthly%20wage%20rate%20(CPI%20Base%20Year%20%3A%202012%20%3D%20100).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20food%20and%20beverages%20and%20fuel%20and%20light%20segments%20under%20the%20rural%20component%20of%20the%20index%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.pib.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2Fspecificdocs%2Fdocuments%2F2023%2Fsep%2Fdoc2023912250801.pdf%5C%22%3Eupward%3C%2Fa%3E%20trend.%20During%20FY%202015-16%2C%20the%20annual%20average%20of%20months%20of%20the%20index%20stood%20at%20118.4%20and%20124.4%20points%2C%20which%20have%C2%A0%20reached%20189.5%20and%20185.9%20with%20an%20inflation%20rate%20around%208.9%25%20and%203.8%25%20respectively%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20alarming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fjean-dreze-writes-wages-are-the-worry-not-just-unemployment-8553226%2F%5C%22%3Estagnation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20real%20wages%2C%20as%20highlighted%20by%20economist%20Jean%20Dreze%2C%20encapsulates%20the%20crisis.%20The%20growth%20rate%20of%20real%20wages%2C%20he%20goes%20on%20to%20show%2C%20was%20below%201%25%20per%20year%20between%202014-15%20and%202021-22.%20It%20was%200.9%25%20for%20agricultural%20labour%20and%200.2%25%20for%20construction%20workers.%20It%20is%20pertinent%20to%20look%20at%20the%20recently%20released%20State%20of%20Working%20India%20Report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fstate-of-working-india%2Fswi-2023%2F%5C%22%3E2023%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20captures%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20a%20dramatic%20rise%20in%20self-employed%20workers%2C%20particularly%20among%20women%2C%20since%20the%20pandemic.%20This%20is%20another%20factor%20that%20pulls%20the%20real%20wages%20down%2C%20given%20that%20the%20self-employed%20saw%20the%20highest%20fall%20in%20earnings%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20war%20the%20only%20factor%20contributing%20to%20the%20price%20rise%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20is%20happy%20to%20externalise%20the%20crisis%20to%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20alone%20and%20its%20effect%20on%20fuel%20prices%2C%20if%20one%20again%20looks%20at%20Figure%20C%20one%20sees%20that%20post%20FY%202020-21%2C%20it%20is%20the%20food%20inflation%20that%20has%20seen%20a%20much%20sharper%20upward%20swing.%20What%20is%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.networkideas.org%2Ffeatured-articles%2F2023%2F09%2Fthe-anatomy-of-inflation%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChandrasekhar%2520and%2520Jayati%2520Ghosh%26amp%3Btext%3DAs%2520news%2520broke%2520that%2520the%2C191.2%2520mm%2520recorded%2520in%25201905.%5C%22%3Edisconcerting%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20economists%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20this%20has%20relatively%20been%20a%20time%20of%20comfortable%20levels%20of%20domestic%20food%20production.%20As%20such%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20apprehended%20below%20normal%20monsoon%20on%20food%20production%20and%20thereby%20on%20the%20already%20high%20food%20prices%20is%20worrying.%20Ironically%20the%20high%20food%20prices%20did%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fdata-stories%2Fdata-focus%2Fwhy-soaring-tomato-prices-have-not-made-farmers-rich%2Farticle67093664.ece%5C%22%3Enot%20benefit%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20farmers%20who%20grow%20the%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20that%20may%20be%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20nonetheless%20look%20at%20the%20fuel%20prices%20and%20its%20supposed%20%E2%80%9Cexternality%E2%80%9D.%20One%20of%20the%20prime%20factors%20behind%20the%20fuel%20prices%20are%20the%20heavy%20taxes.%20One%20of%20the%20major%20sources%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20during%20the%20COVID%20crisis%20was%20through%20taxes%20on%20sale%20of%20fuels%20such%20as%20petrol%20and%20diesel.%20(Bulk%20of%20the%20excise%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.godigit.com%2Ffuel%2Ftaxes%2Fexcise-duty-on-petrol-and-diesel-in-india%5C%22%3Eduty%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20an%20amalgamation%20of%20different%20cess%20and%20thereby%20the%20Union%20does%20not%20even%20have%20to%20share%20revenue%20with%20state%20governments).%20But%20it%20is%20an%20avenue%20of%20tax%20collection%20that%20hurts%20the%20common%20people%20at%20a%20time%20when%20their%20pockets%20were%20the%20shallowest%20owing%20to%20the%20pandemic.%20The%20average%20annual%20tax%20burden%20on%20fuel%20in%20the%20difficult%20years%20of%202020-21%20to%202022-23%20was%20Rs%204.07%20lakh%20crore%20(See%20Figure%20D).%20But%20was%20this%20the%20only%20avenue%20for%20raising%20this%20revenue%3F%20Far%20from%20it.%20In%20a%20country%20that%20is%20witnessing%20one%20of%20the%20most%20grotesque%20inequalities%20between%20the%20top%201%25%20and%20the%20rest%2C%20we%20could%20have%20easily%20raised%20the%20same%20or%20even%20more%20by%20taxing%20the%20wealthiest%20handful.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29152721%2FCLC4.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29152721%2FCLC4.png%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29152721%2FCLC4-300x155.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677518%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22466%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20D%3A%20Trend%20in%20the%20revenue%20generated%20through%20taxes%20%2F%20duties%20that%C2%A0%20Union%20has%20levied%20on%20the%20petroleum%20sector%20over%20the%20years.%C2%A0Source%3A%20Petroleum%20Planning%20%26amp%3B%20Analysis%20Cell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHypothetically%2C%20if%20the%20government%20was%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20the%20enormous%20burden%20of%20rising%20prices%20that%20this%20is%20adding%20to%20the%20common%20people%E2%80%99s%20woes%20and%20had%20revised%20its%20tax%20rates%20to%20the%20pre-pandemic%20(2019-20)%20level%2C%20then%20the%20estimated%20loss%20of%20revenue%20in%20the%20difficult%20years%20would%20have%20been%20Rs%201.19%20lakh%20crore.%20If%20a%20flat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cenfa.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FPrimer-on-Wealth-Inequality.pdf%5C%22%3Ewealth%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20rate%20of%202%25%20was%20imposed%20on%20individuals%20with%20net%20worth%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore%20or%20above%20in%202021%2C%20that%20is%2C%20if%20the%20wealthiest%201%2C007%20families%20in%20the%20country%20were%20taxed%2C%20we%20could%20have%20raised%20Rs%201.84%20lakh%20crore%20in%20just%20a%20year.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxtherichin.wordpress.com%2Fvoices-against-inequality%2F%5C%22%3Ewealth%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20this%20nature%20if%20constituted%20(as%20it%20was%20done%20in%20Argentina%2C%20Bolivia%2C%20Colombia%20and%20so%20on%20after%20the%20pandemic)%20could%20have%20helped%20us%20not%20only%20to%20shield%20the%20poor%20from%20the%20soaring%20fuel%20prices%2C%20but%20also%20recover%20better%20by%20increasing%20welfare%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20we%20tied%20ourselves%20to%20a%20K-shaped%20recovery%20wherein%20rising%20prices%20and%20dwindling%20income%20has%20forced%20the%20poor%20to%20cut%20back%20expenses%20on%20food%20and%20other%20essentials.%20Meanwhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Foff-the-mark-luxury-car-sales-roar-in-india-11690913994834.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAround%252021%252C000%2520luxury%2520cars%2520were%2Cthe%2520same%2520period%2520in%25202018.%255C%5C%22%3Eultra%20rich%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20spending%20on%20imported%20liquor%2C%20luxury%20cars%20and%20leisure%20as%20evidenced%20through%20both%20sales%20and%20import%20data.%20As%20per%20Credit%20Suisse%2C%20the%20number%20of%20USD%20millionaires%20in%20India%20is%20projected%20to%20more%20than%20double%20by%202026.%20Meanwhile%20we%20await%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20hunger%20index%20as%20to%20where%20we%20move%20from%20our%20unenviable%20slippage%20to%20107th%20position.%20Grand%20events%2C%20divisive%20politics%2C%20an%20army%20of%20social%20media%20bots%20and%20a%20pliant%20traditional%20media%20have%20kept%20the%20people%20distracted%20from%20the%20pinch.%20The%20question%20is%2C%20for%20how%20long%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnirban%20Bhattacharya%20is%20Team%20Lead%2C%20National%20Finance%20Team%20and%20Pranay%20Singh%20is%20Data%20Analyst%20at%20Centre%20for%20Financial%20Accountability.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695987012000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3